    <text type="letter">
        <body> 
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_ad.00136_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden<ptr target="loc.04764_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1887-08-17">Aug: 17 '87</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Nothing particular to write ab't. Pleasant weather now for over a week. I am much as
                usual, but cannot move around at all&#8212;Keep good spirits however &amp; am living
                comfortably enough&#8212;Of course lonesomeness &amp; bodily disability are
                dreadful, but things might be so much worse&#8212;Many cases of extreme suffering,
                poverty, sickness, old age &amp;c. around here lately&#8212;As I write I am sitting
                by the open window in the little front sitting room down stairs&#8212;Every thing is
                very quiet&#8212;the expressman is just taking over a big clay head to Phila: to be
                cast&#8212;modeled here by a sculptor<ptr target="n0862"/>&#8212;Best love</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_ad.00135_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
